Adam Matthews: Sunderland full-back joins Bristol City on loan
Bristol City have signed full-back Adam Matthews on a two-month loan deal from Premier League side Sunderland.Matthews has made only two appearances this season since signing on afour-year contract from Celticin July 2015.The 24-year-old has won 12 caps for Wales, but has not featured since a 3-0 defeat by Serbia in September 2013."I want to help the team here first and if my performances warrant a Wales call-up in the summer that'd be brilliant," he told BBC Radio Bristol."In the back of my mind I'd be buzzing if I did go [to the European Championships], but like I said my first aim is to help Bristol City up the table."The Robins currently sit 20th in the Championship, five points above the relegation zone.Find all the latest football transferson our dedicated page.